mij last to you was on the 16 sc. sence recd. yd of 5d. I have no nws
sen
wel
yett of whener goo send hum speedly ovea, I take notice of what you could
have withed, truly, if I slought I could save don you any aggreable seavie
& I could have had the reds & pack whites from other landes, butt whre as
I have had no goods from london from any othe sand thi 12 moncl, so
was loast to give any ot freind the cou, yett I confers. I read this yeae
5 duble reds of a freind knowne to you, butt no spanish clooches, & if you can
make itt apeare, other wise then what I say, I'll loose a £100- for eace
splwish clothe I recd from any other hand butt yd either for my owne or 4
com. though I suppose I cuuld have disposed of 30 spanish cloaches more
then spriny then what I lave don, If I had dad y, frincipolley of
lovely drap cullours low prijses for evor sence apl bill now, wee have had
vere consideable salue, & so much to do, that i reabte I have had no
time to send you the acctt. of sale, butt the worst is that mony doth not
come in accordingly. inclosed some more fatt. which I for spanich
cloaches to yd. gd., yeasterday have payd the other £100- to m taylor his
ad., which please to note accordngly, now shall be for remises &rept on my
accct. dispasch as soone as pou some spanish cloaches principally drap cullours
for I want them. I have pamined the norchres cloaches reed. from you by
diudar, I finde you save not amaided yd. hand most part not laveing
pheir full breach of of a yd, & there by no pennnworcks, so than I cam n

which I do Intmare you because I know you lora our Intrest, sots is drsinguing

Londen M. Willem Scaver
In answer toys of 5 furtt., siever waner is well arrived, & I do eexspect the goods
here verr speedly where yds freind m fore conw reacher shall endeavour to brooke
all my clownnes to entertaince him to the best of my experieny as a fremd
recommended from you, & furmis dim with mony if there unto desired, though
you liit no sume. as to the collicoes designed for m. vale in caso m fabbuton
dogh not aggree aboue them with sard valen & that nime go oft, I'll take them
I have understood they be already att brussel, I must be the with in
& shall ferise the same whillt you shell be able to know what mr. Sabbarton
shall have effected about them, butt I doubt vere much of any complyance
of S.V. the goods that weae designed from the north for mr. vale have been
heept up at daugen, & sij dineekn of m coots sent to smebiden ele, but
by the creditors jeased so shall say no more till I see these now hem
andtheme as brussel

In gevolge ul ad vante desen mijn belofte soo hebbe heden aen ul gesonden
beurtschip 2 dobbel roy laeckens waer van hier in gesloten is de facture
het is het puijexken uyt de partije wenschte wel dat ul deselve t'huys hadde
sonder dat m vander Borght oft artsens de selve saegen, hebbe die sonden tabat
gestelt om dieswille dat het selve op 't aldernauste soude geschieden: Ick hadde
